#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1409
msgid "Codegen-Based Optimizer Module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1411
msgid ""
"Currently, the codegen-based optimizer module provides two optimizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1413
msgid ""
"The first one, available in the legacy code generator, moves literals to the "
"right side of commutative binary operators, which helps exploit their "
"associativity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1416
msgid ""
"The other one, available in the IR-based code generator, enables the use of "
"unchecked arithmetic when generating code for incrementing the counter "
"variable of certain idiomatic ``for`` loops. This avoids wasting gas by "
"identifying some conditions that guarantee that the counter variable cannot "
"overflow. This eliminates the need to use a verbose unchecked arithmetic "
"block inside the loop body to increment the counter variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1426
msgid "Unchecked Loop Increment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1428
msgid ""
"Introduced in Solidity ``0.8.22``, the overflow check optimization step is "
"concerned with identifying the conditions under which the ``for`` loop "
"counter can be safely incremented without overflow checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1432
msgid ""
"This optimization is **only** applied to ``for`` loops of the general form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1434
msgid ""
"for (uint i = X; i < Y; ++i) {\n"
"    // variable i is not modified in the loop body\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1440
msgid ""
"The condition and the fact that the counter variable is only ever "
"incremented guarantee that it never overflows. The precise requirements for "
"the loop to be eligible for the optimization are as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1444
msgid ""
"The loop condition is a comparison of the form ``i < Y``, for a local "
"counter variable ``i`` (called the \"loop counter\" hereon) and an "
"expression ``Y``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1446
msgid ""
"The built-in operator ``<`` is necessarily used in the loop condition and is "
"the only operator that triggers the optimization. ``<=`` and the like are "
"intentionally excluded. Additionally, user-defined operators are **not** "
"eligible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1449
msgid ""
"The loop expression is a prefix or postfix increment of the counter "
"variable, i.e, ``i++`` or ``++i``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1450
msgid "The loop counter is a local variable of a built-in integer type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1451
msgid ""
"The loop counter is **not** modified by the loop body or by the expression "
"used as the loop condition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1452
msgid ""
"The comparison is performed on the same type as the loop counter, meaning "
"that the type of the right-hand-side expression is implicitly convertible to "
"the type of the counter, such that the latter is not implicitly widened "
"before the comparison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1456
msgid "To clarify the last condition, consider the following example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1458
msgid ""
"for (uint8 i = 0; i < uint16(1000); i++) {\n"
"    // ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/optimizer.rst:1464
msgid ""
"In this case, the counter ``i`` has its type implicitly converted from "
"``uint8`` to ``uint16`` before the comparison and the condition is in fact "
"never false, so the overflow check for the increment cannot be removed."
msgstr ""

